-> what is databases?
A database is a collection of data stored in a format taht can easily be accessed.
-> To manage it
We use software DBMS ( Database Management System )
-> Two types of Databases
Relational and Non-Relational (No-SQL)
-> In Relational Databases
We store data in tables using relationships, each tables stores data about a specifc type of object ( order , transaction )
-> SQL or Structured Query Language is we use to quesry or modify our data.
Eg: SELECT * FROM products WHERE category = 'food' ORDER BY price

RDBMS -> MySQL ( Open Source ) , SQL Server ( Microsoft ) and Oracle